<br>
Should police officer's be able to run red lights when they're not on official business?<br>
<br>
Should the Manager of a company be able to, on a personal whim, violate company policies that 'regular' employees must obey?<br>
<br>
Is it ok for a teacher to use prophanity in front of their students, but punish students when they use prophanity in front of the teacher?<br>
<br>
Now, I know that a moderator of a message board does so out of their own free will. Moderators of fan sights such as this one aren't necessarily paid to do so, and are typically under no real legal obligations to perform their duty to a specific standard. <br>
<br>
However, you posed an ethical question. My answer is that if you are enforcing a set of rules, you should live by them too.<br>
<br>
Take a broad view of the United States. I see a lot of problem in this country because there are too many people who are in a position to make decisions that they don't personally have to live with. <br>
<br>
My 2 cents. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usamadhibots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Samadhi BotS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Forum Censor !!!</font></td></tr></table></span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/1/02 4:17:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=890.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question of ethics</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> However, you posed an ethical question. My answer is that if you are enforcing a set of rules, you should live by them too.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
